{"parentUuid":"9cf4b7be-fe74-4028-bf4c-c950100d5ed8","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab361b68186f82ed2","message":{"id":"resp_05750714f323950f0169b9a20b08608199918ef7ca1a58fa97","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"gpt-5.4","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":49285,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":1270,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Compared `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-pm-agent.md` against the three refactor specs.\n\n**ITEM PM-001** — Filesystem-Verified Flag in SelfCheckProtocol  \n- Status: OVERLAPPING\n- Evidence:\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md` §1 states Link 3 “Tasklist -> Code” had “zero programmatic coverage,” and §3.3/§4.4 add a code-level `WIRING_GATE` with STRICT enforcement.\n  - Same spec §4.3 defines a report artifact with filesystem-backed output (`emit_report() -> wiring-report.md`), and §10 SC-001/SC-004/SC-005 make artifact-backed verification a required gate behavior.\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md` §5.2 says unknown/missing deterministic inputs fail, and §5.3 requires evidence references for failed checks.\n- Recommendation: REVISE — keep the PM-agent-local `filesystem_verified` concept, but align its meaning to the new gate vocabulary. Instead of treating mere file existence as sufficient proof, define it as alignment with artifact-backed deterministic evidence, ideally referencing wiring-gate findings when the claim is about Tasklist→Code completion. The item is still useful because v3.0/v3.1 add pipeline gate artifacts, not a PM Agent return-field on `SelfCheckProtocol.validate()`.\n\n**ITEM PM-002** — Mandatory Negative Evidence Documentation in SelfCheckProtocol  \n- Status: OVERLAPPING\n- Evidence:\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md` §5.2 requires deterministic failure on missing evidence, and §5.3 requires every failed check to carry evidence references.\n  - Same spec §6.1 requires `checks[]` with severity + evidence, reinforcing explicit evidence accounting.\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md` §1, §3, and module sections consistently frame validation as deterministic evidence production, especially for omissions and coverage gaps.\n- Recommendation: REVISE — keep the item, but narrow it to PM Agent observability rather than treating it as a new repo-wide evidence model. The refactors already standardize explicit evidence for failures; what remains unique here is recording clean-check “nothing found” results as first-class PM-agent outputs (`negative_evidence`). That is additive, not replaced.\n\n**ITEM PM-003** — Model Tier Proportionality for PM Agent Operations  \n- Status: OVERLAPPING\n- Evidence:\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md` §3.2 makes `profile` the canonical runtime policy input.\n  - Same spec §10.2 item 5 says `src/superclaude/agents/*.md` changes are “enrichment-only role clarification.”\n  - Same spec §11 and §12 list unresolved profile thresholds / major-severity behavior as open blocking decisions, meaning policy ownership is being centralized in the audit-gating model rather than individual agent docs.\n- Recommendation: REVISE — keep the `src/superclaude/pm_agent/__init__.py` documentation if desired, but remove or sharply limit the `.claude/agents/pm-agent.md` behavioral policy portion. In the post-v3.1 world, agent markdown should be role clarification only, while canonical runtime policy belongs in the centralized profile/policy system. Also rename or remap “tier” language to avoid conflict with v3.1’s profile/tier terminology.\n\n**ITEM PM-004** — ReflexionPattern: Presumption of Falsehood Default Stance  \n- Status: UNAFFECTED\n- Evidence:\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md` is scoped to code wiring analysis in CLI audit/sprint infrastructure; it does not define ReflexionPattern confidence semantics.\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md` targets roadmap-generation failure modes in `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/`, not PM-agent solution retrieval.\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md` defines audit-gate contracts and agent-file role clarification, but does not replace `ReflexionPattern.get_solution()` / `record_error()` confidence handling.\n- Recommendation: KEEP-AS-IS — this item remains independent of the three refactors.\n\nOverall, `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-pm-agent.md` is not obsolete, but it should not be carried forward unchanged: PM-001 and PM-002 now need alignment with the refactored deterministic evidence/gating model, PM-003 needs the most adjustment because v3.1 centralizes policy and limits `agents/*.md` to enrichment-only clarification, and PM-004 remains largely standalone."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn"},"type":"assistant","uuid":"6baed309-a2aa-4c31-ab06-b79ae5a22379","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:49:08.345Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
